### For your Arthur Core flow

I would have:

| Scenario                               | Page                         |
| -------------------------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| Sales point selected successfully      | Success status               |
| No sales points returned from Lancelot | Sales Point Not Defined      |
| Lancelot timeout                       | Technical Error              |
| Redis unavailable                      | Technical Error              |
| Ping unavailable                       | Technical Error              |
| Invalid AppId                          | Technical Error              |
| Unauthorized user                      | Dedicated Access Denied page |

The only page I'd keep separate is:

```text
access-denied.html
```

because that's a different business scenario than an application failure.

So your final structure becomes:

```text
sales-point-selection.html
status-page.html
access-denied.html
```

instead of maintaining 5–6 separate Thymeleaf pages. This will be much easier to maintain as Arthur Core grows and more applications (B2BOOST_BE, B2BOOST_NL, etc.) are onboarded.


